AB  - Species reintroductions are high-investment ecological interventions that require careful planning. Predictive models are useful tools for managing reintroductions.
   We provide an overview of habitat suitability, dispersal, population dynamics and interspecies models, considering potential uses and limitations of established methods for reintroductions. Furthermore, we include a guide for integrating one or more model types to predict reintroduction outcomes and answer specific management questions.
